description.description: On November 6, 2020, Illinois announced that they "will report confirmed cases and probable cases combined” going forward rather than reporting them separately. The time series for the Confirmed and Probable Case metrics are available in the historical data, and our data downloads.

childMarkdownRemark.html: On November 6, 2020, Illinois announced that they “will report confirmed cases and probable cases combined” going forward rather than reporting them separately. The time series for the Confirmed and Probable Case metrics are available in the historical data, and our data downloads.

nodes.full_text: The changes in ME dropped totalTestResults by around 40k. The changes in IL made no impact to the value of totalTestResults at the topline but may have shifted earlier values.
For our API users: Yesterday, we switched totalTestResults to use values from totalTestsViral instead of being calculated from positive+negative in 4 states: IL, ME, MI, and SD.

As of today, vaccine data is readily available across 49 states and territories, but our team only found vaccine data on doses administered in LTCs in seven states: Arkansas, Illinois, Kentucky, Michigan, South Carolina, Tennessee, and Texas.
Seven states reported more than 10k cases today: CA, FL, IL, NY, PA, OH, and TX. https://t.co/L93HHx9vjH

The Midwest remains the epicenter of COVID-19 in long-term care facilities. The region has seen the highest number of reported LTC cases & deaths every week since mid-November. Four states—IL, OH, IN & MN—topped the nation in new reported LTC deaths last week. https://t.co/bp1sBO7RmF

nodes.warning: According to its website, IL includes antigen tests in this metric.
